author: Inside Edition
description: A 54-year-old man admitted to killing his elderly parents, he says, to put them out of their misery. Lorenz Kraus' parents disappeared eight years ago, but they were still collecting social security benefits. Police obtained a search warrant and the remains were found in their backyard. Hours later, Kraus reached out to CBS 6 and described how he says he killed them in 2017. After the interview, Kraus walked outside where he was arrested. A public defender entered a not guilty plea for Kraus.
title: Man Confesses To Killing His Parents In TV Interview

author: Inside Edition
description: An ICE agent has reportedly been placed on administrative leave after video showed him push a woman to the ground during a confrontation. It happened in New York City outside of an immigration courtroom. Reports say the woman is the wife of a man from Nicaragua who showed up to court, only to be taken into custody by ICE agents. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: ICE Agent Placed on Leave After Pushing Woman To Ground In New York: Reports

author: Inside Edition
description: Two young kids jumped into action when 35-year-old Sarah James passed out at home in Gillette, Wyoming. When the mother realized she was having an allergic reaction possibly to medication from recent knee surgery. Her kids had just come home from school, and she told them to urgently call her best friend and their grandparents. Surveillance tape shows a police officer and the children's grandmother racing to the house. The family spoke with Inside Edition.
title: Hero Kids Save Mom's Life After Allergic Reaction To Medication

author: Inside Edition
description: Deborah Brashers is speaking out as police announced a breakthrough in the so-called Yogurt Shop Murders. The victims were Jennifer Harbison, her sister Sara, and their friends Amy Ayers and Eliza Thomas. The teens were found slain at a yogurt shop in Austin, Texas, in 1991. The slayings are the subject of the new HBO docu-series "The Yogurt Shop Murders." Police say Brashers' father, Robert Eugene Brashers, is behind the crime, established by new DNA technology.
title: Daughter of Suspected Yogurt Shop Murders Killer Speaks Out

author: Inside Edition
description: Prosecutors say former Marine Sergeant Nigel Max Edge opened fire on diners at a popular restaurant in North Carolina Saturday night, killing three and wounding eight. Thirteen years ago the Marine sniper accompanied country music star Kellie Pickler to the Country Music Television Awards and spoke with Inside Edition's Megan Alexander. He suffered from PTSD and brought along his service dog. Police say on Saturday he opened fire from his boat on diners at the American Fish Company restaurant.
title: NC Shooting Suspect Accompanied Kellie Pickler To CMT Awards In 2012

author: Inside Edition
description: Polar bears have taken over a tiny town on an island in the Chukchi Sea, on the far east coast of #Russia.
title: Polar Bears Take Over Abandoned Town #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: These days, it’s getting harder to tell what video is real and what’s been manipulated by AI. Social media is flooded with AI-deepfakes of doctors and celebrities, many of them who appear to be selling a weight loss supplement called the “Pink Salt Trick.” INSIDE EDITION tracked down Dr. Rachel Goldman, who told us that she was the victim of an AI-deepfake that appeared to present her as the creator of the “Pink Salt Trick.”
title: Celebrities Were Deepfaked In Videos for Weight Loss Hack

author: Inside Edition
description: Kendall Chrisman from California is living with one of the most inconvenient allergies there is.
title: Young Swimmer Is Allergic To Water #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Could this woman hold the secrets to living longer? She was the oldest person alive for a time, but Maria Branyas Morera died last year at age 117. She told her family that upon her death she wanted to be studied to learn what kept her going. Researchers in Spain say Morera never smoked or drank and her diet was typical for people living in the Mediterranean. She especially loved yogurt, which she is said to have had several times per day. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Did Eating Lots of Yogurt Help This Woman Live to 117?

author: Inside Edition
description: Police in #Seattle say they tried to pull over a vehicle, which they say had a #stolen license plate, but the driver wouldn't stop.
title: Fleeing Car Jumps Open Drawbridge #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Parents said painful blisters on their teens’ hands came after their coach ordered them to do bear crawls along a hot track as punishment during majorette practice.
title: Teens Got Painful Blisters From Dance Coach's Punishment: Parents #shorts
